2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves the development and evaluation of a machine learning model for solar power forecasting. 
3. cs.SD (Software Engineering): While not the main focus of the paper, the development and implementation of the support vector regression model for solar power forecasting involves software engineering principles and techniques. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper compares the performance of the support vector regression model with artificial neural networks for energy forecasting. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper's focus on energy forecasting and load balancing in the smart grid involves systems and control principles and techniques.
